review_blob: Cold 50cL can. A grainy aroma. It looks dark amber with a medium head. A light sweet taste with a bitter and alcoholic aftertaste. Overall a nice beer.
Cold 50cL can, clear amber colour. A sweet aroma and a poor head. It tastes very sweet with a hint of honey. Overall a decent beer.
Cold 33cL bottle, very very sweet taste, light brown colour and a good head. Overall it is too sweet and what youd expect from cookie beer, it tastes like cookie.
Cold 33cL bottle, very hazy yellow appearance, a very sweet aroma and with a sweet taste. This beer has a great body but sadly not a lot of head. Overall a very nice beer.
Cold, bottled 25cL . Weak head. Hazy yellow appearance. Tastes sweet and smooth. Fruity aroma.
